The values of that entity should be `var data: String?` with a constructor:

    @Entity
    data class User(
        @PrimaryKey val id: Int,
        var firstName: String?,
        var lastName: String?,
        @Ignore var picture: Bitmap?
    ){
      constructor: this(firstName = &quot;&quot;, lastName = &quot;&quot;)
    }

Of course you can do `val`s , but you should add constructor.

Or just `val`s:

    @Entity
    data class User(
        @PrimaryKey val id: Int,
        var firstName: String,
        var lastName: String,
        @Ignore var picture: Bitmap
    )

So really, `@Ignore` has nothing to do with that. For more, [refer this article][1]. 

You can&#39;t really have `val`s and nulls at the same time. Room doesn&#39;t allow that. If you want your variables to be nullable stick to `var` and add constructor to the data class as described above.

